JOHANNESBURG - Energy Minister Jeff Radebe has signed the agreements for 27 renewable-energy independent power producer projects, which have been delayed since 2016. The projects have a collective investment value of R56-billion. READ:Â Numsa, Transform RSA block energy deals The agreements include power-purchase agreements with Eskom. Radebe says the signings follow a long period of uncertainty. In early 2016, Eskom had indicated it was unwilling to enter into new purchasing agreements with independent power producers, having returned to a surplus operating position. eNCA